@startuml
title Runtime Seam Sketch - Focus Slice (Event/Message First)
left to right direction
skinparam componentStyle rectangle

package "Foundational Runtime Modules" {
  component "core" as CORE
  component "debug" as DBG
  component "render" as RND
  component "player" as PLY
}

package "USF Runtime Modules" {
  component "chunk (USF-specific)" as CHK
  component "usf" as USF
  component "rhai_binding" as RHAI
}

note right of CHK
Chunk remains USF-specific.
Chunk identity: ChunkId(GridVec).
UnitVec models intra-chunk local state.
Chunk should publish boundary/lifecycle events/messages,
not directly own gameplay entity materialization.
end note

PLY -[#43A047]-> CHK : emits player anchor updates (GridVec/UnitVec context)
CHK -[#43A047]-> USF : emits boundary lifecycle + boundary delta events/messages
USF -[#43A047]-> CHK : emits realization directives (genesis/evolve feedback)

RHAI -[#43A047]-> USF : emits typed script-entrypoint intents
USF -[#8E24AA]-> RHAI : emits runtime snapshots + diagnostics facts

CORE -[#43A047]-> RND : emits proxy/runtime coordination directives
RND -[#8E24AA]-> CORE : emits render/runtime telemetry facts

DBG -[#8E24AA]-> CORE : subscribes runtime facts for inspection
DBG -[#43A047]-> CORE : emits debug/tool intents
DBG -[#8E24AA]-> USF : subscribes USF runtime facts

note bottom
This diagram is a seam sketch, not final API naming.
Delivery semantics are intentionally not locked yet:
- broadcast-like runtime facts
- consumable/authority-routed directives/intents
end note
@enduml
